content:
Test Your Apple Messages for Business Channel in Service Cloud

You're required to have Enhanced Apple Messages for Business channels.

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
View Setup and Configuration to send and receive messages in Messaging.
End Messaging Session to end messaging sessions.

We recommend creating separate Apple Messages for Business accounts for sandbox and production.

ACTION

(Optional) Set up Messaging in your sandbox.
Match your sandbox org licenses to your production org.
Complete the steps in Get Started with Messaging.
Create your Apple Messages for Business channel using the account you designated for sandbox testing.

Test your channel in sandbox or production:

Log into Salesforce as an agent.
Open the app that contains Messaging.
Change your Omni-Channel presence status to online and available.
From a personal Apple Messages account, send a message to the associated channel account.
Exchange messages, experiment with sending images, files, and messaging components, and test auto-responses.

When done, click End Chat.

(Optional) Migrate changes from sandbox to production by creating a change set or manually repeating setup steps.
title: Testing Apple Messages for Business Channel in Service Cloud
